{"key":"processedPost-8840844","value":{"id":8840844,"first":8832966,"last":8840844,"when":1219939684,"utime":"08/28/08 07:08 PM","content":"A few chunks are fine.&nbsp; In my <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">brf tek video</a>, fellow shroomery moderator Roadkill made a batch that still had a few small chunks, but most was ground to about the size of beach sand.&nbsp; <br />To prevent getting a 'paste' at the bottom, mix the water and verm first, and then slowly stir in the rice flour.&nbsp; If you mix the rice flour and verm first, you'll end up with a paste at the bottom, which is a common first-timer mistake.&nbsp; Live and learn.<br />RR","title":"Re: How fine should I grind the brown rice for pf cakes?"}}